#. type: Title =
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "Processing of Taxonomic Identifiers in GBIF "
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:13
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/standards-publishing.adoc:14
msgid "include::ROOT::partial$under-construction.adoc[]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:15
msgid "GBIF processes taxonomic identifiers that are provided on the DwC elements _scientificNameID_, _taxonID_ and _taxonConceptID_, when these identifiers belong to any of the identifier schemes available. The identifiers are retrieved from ChecklistBank and linked to taxa in the checklist. Currently, the schemes available are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:17
msgid "https://artfakta.se/metadata/dyntaxa[Dyntaxa]: A taxonomic database of the names of Swedish organisms, which contains information on current classification, recommended names and commonly used synonyms and misused names. It should follow the format:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:19
msgid "`+^(?:dyntaxa|artfakta|urn:lsid:dyntaxa.se:Taxon):(\\\\d+)`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Example*: urn:lsid:dyntaxa.se:Taxon:106661\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://www.ipni.org/[IPNI]: The International Plant Names Index (IPNI) is a nomenclatural index of names of vascular plants published under the Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi and plants (ICN).  It should follow the format: \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:24
msgid "`+^(?:ipni|urn:lsid:ipni.org:names):(\\\\d+-[1-3])`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Example*: urn:lsid:ipni.org:names:50959-2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://www.itis.gov/[ITIS]: The Integrated Taxonomic Information System, an authoritative taxonomic information on plants, animals, fungi, and microbes of North America and the world. It should follow the format: \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:29
msgid "`+^(?:itis|tsn:)(\\\\d+)`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Example*: tsn:80028\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://www.nhm.ac.uk/our-science/data/uk-species/index[UK Species Inventory]: A database of all UK wildlife, which provides the taxonomic foundation for most biological recording and analysis systems for the UK. It should follow the format: \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:34
msgid "`+^(?:uksi|nhm):((?:NHMSYS|NBNSYS)\\\\d{10})`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Example*: nhm:NBNSYS0000161229\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://www.marinespecies.org/index.php[WoRMS]: The World Register of Marine Species (WoRMS) aims to provide an authoritative and comprehensive list of names of marine organisms, including information on synonymy. It should follow the format: \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:39
msgid "`+^(?:marinespecies|worms|aphia|urn:lsid:marinespecies.org:taxname):(\\\\d+)`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:41
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Example*: urn:lsid:marinespecies.org:taxname:538339\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:44
msgid "When both an identifier field and a _scientificName_ are provided, the identifiers will be used first for matching, and if there is more than one identifier present, the information on _taxonID_ will take precedence. A match will also be made using the _scientificName_, and a comparison will be made between the two matches."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://techdocs.gbif.org/en/data-use/occurrence-issues-and-flags#taxonomic-issues[Taxonomic flags and issues] are assigned during https://techdocs.gbif.org/en/data-processing/taxonomy-interpretation#taxonomic-indexes[pipeline processing] if inconsistencies are detected in the applied identifiers.   \n"
msgstr ""

